  "body": "As a developer/tester, I want to test wallet looks and acts correctly when user owns ERC20 tokens.\r\n\r\nIt's fairly easy to get some ETH in your account to test transfers and so on, but we don't have a solution for getting ERC20 tokens associated to an account. In order to add tokens to the wallet I think we need to figure out some workflow with this.\r\n\r\nOptions: \r\n-  1) mock it\r\n- 2) ignore it for now\r\n- 3) figure out a simple way to sign ERC20 contracts similar to faucet\r\n- 4) do it outside of the app and re-use account somehow\r\n\r\nAfter discussion in Slack:\r\n\r\n- (3) We need to deploy contract, send some amount of tokens to faucetâ€™s address and then send these tokens from faucet\r\n\r\nPossibly get help from Commiteth team with deploying contract, they also have some kind of STT test token.\r\n\r\nAcceptance criteria:\r\n- A simple way for individual developers and testers to get ERC20 tokens in their account",
